8 Be it enacted by the Legislature of the State of Kansas:
9 Section 1. K.S.A. 40-108 is hereby amended to read as follows: 40-
10 108. The commissioner of insurance shall make an annual report to the
11 governor of the general conduct and condition of the insurance companies,
12 including fraternal benefit societies, doing business in this state. The
13 commissioner of insurance shall make an annual report of the general
14 conduct and condition of the insurance companies, including fraternal
15 benefit societies, doing business in this state and shall publish such
16 report on the department's website. The commissioner of insurance shall
17 keep and preserve in a permanent form a full record of the commissioner's
18 proceedings, including a concise statement of the condition of each
19 company reported, visited or examined by the commissioner.
20 Sec. 2. K.S.A. 2024 Supp. 40-2,125 is hereby amended to read as
21 follows: 40-2,125. (a) If the commissioner determines after notice and
22 opportunity for a hearing that any person has engaged or is engaging in
23 any act or practice constituting a violation of any provision of Kansas
24 insurance statutes or any rule and regulation or order thereunder, the
25 commissioner may, in the exercise of discretion, order any one or more of
26 the following:
27 (1) Payment of a monetary penalty of not more than $1,000 for each
28 and every act or violation, unless the person knew or reasonably should
29 have known that such person was in violation of the Kansas insurance
30 statutes or any rule and regulation or order thereunder, in which case the
31 penalty shall be not more than $2,000 for each and every act or violation;
32 (2) suspension or revocation of the person's license or certificate if
33 such person knew or reasonably should have known that such person was
34 in violation of the Kansas insurance statutes or any rule and regulation or

