2 (3) that such person cease and desist from the unlawful act or practice
3 and take such affirmative action as that, in the judgment of the
4 commissioner, will carry out the purposes of the violated or potentially
5 violated provision.
6 (b) If any person fails to file any report or other information with the
7 commissioner as required by statute or fails to respond to any proper
8 inquiry of the commissioner, the commissioner, after notice and
9 opportunity for hearing, may impose a civil penalty of up to $1,000, for
10 each violation or act, along with an additional penalty of up to $500 for
11 each week thereafter that such report or other information is not provided
12 to the commissioner.
13 (c) If the commissioner makes written findings of fact that there is a
14 situation involving an immediate danger to the public health, safety or
15 welfare or the public interest will be irreparably harmed by delay in
16 issuing an order under subsection (a)(3), the commissioner may issue an
17 emergency temporary cease and desist order. Such order, even when not an
18 order within the meaning of K.S.A. 77-502, and amendments thereto, shall
19 be subject to the same procedures as an emergency order issued under
20 K.S.A. 77-536, and amendments thereto. Upon the entry of such an order,
21 the commissioner shall promptly notify the person subject to the order
22 that: (1) It Such order has been entered; (2) the reasons therefor; and (3)
23 that upon written request within 15 days after service of the order, the
24 matter will be set for a hearing, which shall be conducted in accordance
25 with the provisions of the Kansas administrative procedure act. If no
26 hearing is requested and none is ordered by the commissioner, the order
27 will remain in effect until it is modified or vacated by the commissioner. If
28 a hearing is requested or ordered, the commissioner, after notice of and
29 opportunity for hearing to the person subject to the order, shall, by written
30 findings of fact and conclusions of law vacate, modify or make permanent
31 the order.
32 (d) For purposes of this section:
33 (1) "Person" means any individual, corporation, association,
34 partnership, reciprocal exchange, inter-insurer, Lloyd's insurer, fraternal
35 benefit society and any other legal entity engaged in the business of
36 insurance, rating organization, third party administrator, nonprofit dental
