5 Sec. 3. K.S.A. 40-2253 is hereby amended to read as follows: 40-
6 2253. (a) The commissioner of insurance shall devise universal forms to be
7 utilized by every insurance company, including health maintenance
8 organizations where applicable, offering any type of accident and sickness
9 policy covering individuals residing in this state for the purpose of
10 receiving every claim under such policy by persons covered thereunder. In
11 the preparation of such forms, the commissioner may confer with
12 representatives of insurance companies, health maintenance organizations,
13 trade associations and other interested parties. Upon completion and final
14 adoption of such forms by the commissioner, the commissioner shall
15 notify those companies affected by sending them a copy of such forms and
16 an explanation of the requirements of this section. Every such company
17 shall implement utilization of such forms not later than six months
18 following the date of the commissioner's notification.
19 (b) An accident and sickness insurer may not refuse to accept a claim
20 submitted on duly promulgated uniform claim forms. An insurer may
21 accept claims submitted on any other form.
22 (c) An accident and sickness insurer does not violate subsection (a)
23 by using a document that the accident and sickness insurer has been
24 required to use by the federal government or the state.
25 (d) The commissioner of insurance shall report to the governor and to
26 the legislature, no later than the commencement of the 1993 regular
27 session of the Kansas legislature, regarding the development of uniform
28 electronic data interchange formats and standards, along with a proposed
29 plan, including an analysis of the cost impact thereof.
30 Sec. 4. K.S.A. 40-108 and 40-2253 and K.S.A. 2024 Supp. 40-2,125
31 are hereby repealed.
32 Sec. 5. This act shall take effect and be in force from and after its
33 publication in the statute book Kansas register.

